# 🎓 Global College LMS — Comprehensive System Review

> **Project:** Edu-Sphere / Global College LMS  
> **Review Date:** May 5, 2026  
> **Status:** Early-stage prototype — ~15% complete  

---

## 1. Executive Summary

The Global College LMS project was scaffolded by Replit AI as a **pnpm monorepo** using Replit's proprietary workspace architecture. While the project has database schemas for 17 tables, 21 API route files, and frontend pages for all three roles (Student, Teacher, Admin), **nearly everything is a non-functional shell**. The backend uses **in-memory sessions** instead of JWT, has **no authentication middleware**, no role-based access control, and no file upload capability. The frontend pages display static/mock data with no real CRUD operations working end-to-end. The project is also **100% dependent on Replit infrastructure** — it cannot run independently.

---

## 2. Architecture Overview — What Exists

### Current Folder Structure
```
Edu-Sphere/
├── .replit, .npmrc, .replitignore      ← Replit-specific config
├── pnpm-workspace.yaml                 ← Replit workspace with platform overrides
├── package.json                        ← Root workspace (pnpm)
├── tsconfig.base.json                  
├── lib/
│   ├── db/                             ← Drizzle ORM schemas (17 tables)
│   ├── api-spec/                       ← OpenAPI YAML spec (auto-generated)
│   ├── api-zod/                        ← Zod validation schemas
│   └── api-client-react/               ← Auto-generated React Query hooks
├── artifacts/
│   ├── api-server/                     ← Express.js backend
│   ├── global-college/                 ← React + Vite frontend
│   └── mockup-sandbox/                 ← Design mockup (unused)
├── scripts/                            ← Post-merge scripts
└── attached_assets/                    ← Requirements docs
```

### Tech Stack (Current)
| Layer | Technology | Status |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| Frontend | React 19 + Vite 7 + TailwindCSS 4 + Radix UI | Shell pages exist |
| Backend | Express 5 + TypeScript | Route files exist, minimal logic |
| Database | PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM | Schemas defined, no migrations verified |
| Auth | In-memory Map sessions (SHA-256) | ❌ Not production-ready |
| Routing | Wouter (client-side) | Basic routes defined |
| State | React Query + auto-generated hooks | Hooks exist but most fail |
| Styling | TailwindCSS + shadcn/ui components | UI components installed |

