## 6. Routing Structure Problems

The current routing does **not follow the required URL pattern**:

| Required | Current | Issue |
|----------|---------|-------|
| `/student/dashboard` | `/dashboard` | Missing `/student` prefix |
| `/student/courses` | `/dashboard/courses` | Wrong prefix |
| `/student/courses/:id/learn` | `/dashboard/lessons/:courseId` | Wrong pattern |
| `/teacher/dashboard` | `/teacher` | Minor |
| `/teacher/courses/:id/edit` | Not exists | Missing |
| `/admin/dashboard` | `/admin` | Minor |
| `/admin/students/:id` | Not exists | Missing |
| `/admin/teachers/:id` | Not exists | Missing |
| `/courses/:slug` | `/courses/:id` | Should use slug not ID |

---

## 7. Database Schema Problems

### Missing Relationships
```
Users ←→ Branches      (branchId FK missing from users)
Courses ←→ Sections    (Section model doesn't exist)
Sections ←→ Lessons    (sectionId FK missing from lessons)
Lessons ←→ Quizzes     (lessonId FK missing)
Lessons ←→ Assignments (lessonId FK missing)
```

### Using Integer IDs vs CUIDs
- Current: `serial("id")` (auto-increment integers)
- Required: `cuid()` string IDs (per PRD)
- **Decision needed**: Integers are fine for PostgreSQL, but the PRD specifies CUIDs

### Missing Indexes
No database indexes defined on any table — will cause performance issues at scale.

### Missing Constraints
- No unique constraint on `enrollments(userId, courseId)`
- No unique constraint on `lessonProgress(userId, lessonId)`
- Course `slug` field doesn't exist (no SEO-friendly URLs)

